I understand why people don&#x27;t like ORMs. But I don&#x27;t understand people who like iBatis: it is boilerplate like the hell. Imaging you have to separately update mappings for SQL select, insert, update and delete query (and these mappings are very long) for your entities.<p>For example, prepared statement for update looks like this:<p><pre><code>  PreparedStatement ps = ...;
  ps.setLong(1, author.getUserId());
  ps.setLong(2, author.getStreamId());
  ps.setString(3, author.getNetwork());
  ps.setString(4, author.getIdInNetwork());
  ps.setString(5, author.getNote());
  ps.setString(6, author.getSocialId());
</code></pre>
....<p>And manually counting questions is a normal practice when you add a field:<p><pre><code>  static final String UPDATE = &quot;UPDATE Table1 SET Domains = ?, TemplateId = ?, InternalJson = ? WHERE StreamID = ?&quot;;
  static final String INSERT = &quot;INSERT INTO Config1 (UserID, StreamID, Domains, TemplateId, InternalJson) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)&quot;;</code></pre>
